<Paragraph>
Charts are visually appealing and make it easy for users to see comparisons, patterns, and trends in data. 
Excel offers many different chart options, such as pie charts, columns, bars, 
lines, and area charts.
</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">Features:</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>

<Paragraph>
In Excel, charts are created using the following four steps in the Chart Wizard.
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Select a chart type.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Set "Data-Range" options.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Insert a title for the chart.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Select whether the chart is to be embedded in the current worksheet or placed on a separate chart sheet.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

